headline.main: RETURN OF THE U. S. SHIP DALE.; Arrival of the Dale from a Two Years' Cruise on the Coast of Africa--United States Coal Depot at Porte Grande-Fine and Imprisonment of an American Citizen--Cruising of the Dale and Vincennes.

docs.lead_paragraph: The Dale has just returned home from the Coast of Africa, after an absence of more than two years. For several weeks awaiting a summons to the land which none love better those who have long been exiles,we were anchored at Porto Praya. Anything more arid, leafless and calcined than that wretched little Portuguese town, and its background of volcanic peaks, perhaps does not exist.

docs.lead_paragraph: DEATH OF CHARLES R. LESLIE, R. A. The last English papers announce the death of the celebrated painter, CHARLES R. LESLIE, R. A., who died in London suddenly of disease of the heart, at the age of 65. Mr. LESLIE has always been regarded as an American, though he was born in London, where he lived the greater part of his life, and where he gained his reputation.

docs.lead_paragraph: The election in Virginia takes place on Thursday next, the 26th inst. For several months a very animated canvass has been in progress, Messrs. LETCHER and GOGGIN, the candidates of the Democrats and Opposition respectively, for Governor, meeting each other in different parts of the State for public discussion.
